1. Ja sam ispričao priču svojoj prijateljici. (I told a story to my friend.) *Ispričao* is in the past tense.
2. On će ispričati vic na zabavi večeras. (He will tell a joke at the party tonight.) *Ispričati* is in the future tense.
3. Kada si ti ispričao tu laž? (When did you tell that lie?) *Ispričao* is in the past tense and used in a question.
4. Nisam ispričao sve detalje jer nisam znao da li te zanimaju. (I didn't tell all the details because I didn't know if you were interested.) *Ispričao* is in the past tense and used negatively.
5. Molim te, ispričaj mi šta se dogodilo sinoć. (Please tell me what happened last night.) *Ispričaj* is in the imperative form and used as a request.
6. On je već ispričao tu priču pet puta, ne moraš ponavljati. (He has already told that story five times, you don't have to repeat it.) *Ispričao* is in the past tense and used in a comparative sentence.
7. Kada budemo sjeli da ručamo, ispričaću ti vic koji sam čuo juče. (When we sit down to eat, I will tell you a joke I heard yesterday.) *Ispričaću* is in the future tense.
8. Ovaj roman je ispričan iz perspektive glavnog lika. (This novel is told from the perspective of the main character.) *Ispričan* is in the past participle form and used to describe the state of the novel.